/* Studies and reports */ This paragraph needed editing. Charlebois oped, did not "deride" people who steal food in supermarkets. This was a misleading statement. Also, fail to see how Charlebois' personal salary is relevant to this information. More importantly, citations used to support this paragraph use Twitter as a source, and only Twitter which goes against Wikipedia rules. I would recommend deleting this paragraph altogether.

/* Career */ This is an important addition, which is clearly mentioned in the citation, almost verbatim. The former sentence implied Charlebois did something wrong, and was not able to find any citation suggesting that Charlebois was guilty. Given allegations, it is critical for the Wiki community to know that Charlebois was not sanctioned. Also, deleted irrelevant information about Charlebois' thought process before his resignation.
/* Career */  Corrected passage to reflect cited article accurately.
